OL,3,CFerry workers to vote on strikes over
OL,4,Cjobs
OL,6,F"Unless Wightlink management withdraws
OL,7,Fthese proposals and gives guarantees
OL,8,Fto maintain the highest standards of
OL,9,Fsafety and decent, secure jobs, we
OL,10,Fwill take action to defend our members
OL,11,Fand the communities they serve."
OL,13,FIn a statement Wightlink said: "We are
OL,14,Fdisappointed by the RMT's decision to
OL,15,Fballot for strike action when we are
OL,16,Fopenly working with them to discuss
OL,17,Fthe proposal and consider colleague
OL,18,Ffeedback. The proposal they are
OL,19,Fballoting on is still in negotiation
OL,20,Fand we are committed to finding an
OL,21,Fagreed outcome.
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}   G3/5
